³ Bello tentare] Tentare is here put for tentabant, a mode of ex- pression familiar not only to Sallust, but usual in most historians 3 who, to render their periods smooth and glib, and make their language keep pace, in some sort, with the quickness of the actions they would ex- press, and with the fire of their own imagination, generally affect the use of infinitives, and neglect the indicatives as more clogged and heavy.
